    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="1156"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1156">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">860c.24/7–2645: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1156<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chief of the Division of Lend-Lease and Surplus <gloss
                            target="#t_War1">War</gloss> Property Affairs</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_FFW1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fetter</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Assistant Secretary of State</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_CWL1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clayton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">and the Director of the Office of Financial and
                        Development Policy</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CEG1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Collado</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d1156fn1">Sent to the Secretary of State at
                        Babelsberg over the signature of <persName corresp="#p_GJC1"
                        >Grew</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extracts]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-28">July 28
                            [1945.]</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>154. For <persName corresp="#p_CWL1">Clayton</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_CEG1">Collado</persName> from <persName corresp="#p_FFW1"
                        >Fetter</persName>.</p>
                <p>On July 18 <gloss target="#t_OANLC1">OANLC</gloss> instructed Field Commissioner
                    Paris (Your <gloss target="#t_Victory1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Victory</hi>
                    </gloss> 349 July 26<note n="2" xml:id="d1156fn2">
                        <ref target="#d1155">Document No. 1155</ref>.</note>) to make all necessary
                    arrangements for delivery of 1,000 trucks to Polish Govt. Ambassador <persName
                        corresp="#p_LAB1">Lane</persName> has discussed question with Field
                    Commissioner and reports that approximately <pb facs="1352" n="1154"
                        xml:id="pg_1154"/> 750 trucks for Poland are available in U. K. for early
                    delivery and that remaining 250 could be obtained on Continent. We do not know
                    what official of Polish Govt should execute necessary documents and accept
                    delivery. <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> has instructed <persName
                        corresp="#p_LAB1">Lane</persName> to request Polish Govt to name
                    representative to close transaction. <persName corresp="#p_LAB1"
                    >Lane</persName>, now in Paris, reports that he will do this on his arrival in
                    Warsaw about July 30. Nothing more can be done until <persName corresp="#p_LAB1"
                        >Lane</persName> and Polish Govt supply further information. <gloss
                        target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_OANLC1">OANLC</gloss>
                    feel that no public announcement of truck deal should be made until all
                    arrangements are completed and <persName corresp="#p_LAB1">Lane</persName> has
                    been instructed not to release public statement without first submitting it to
                    Washington.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>This reply has been shown to <gloss target="#t_OANLC1">OANLC</gloss> and they
                    concur in respect to any actions by them.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
